<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Flare" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="2" MadCap:lastHeight="139" MadCap:lastWidth="747">
    <body>
        <p>You can base the heading levels on the structure you create in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">outline TOC</MadCap:conditionalText>. If <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">a TOC</MadCap:conditionalText> entry is at the extreme left of the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">TOC</MadCap:conditionalText> Editor, it will display at the first level of the print TOC; if an entry is indented to the right one level, it will display at the second level; and so on. Not only will those headings be reflected in the generated TOC in the output, but the corresponding headings will be converted in the main body too (e.g., if a heading becomes an h2 in the TOC, it will become an h2 in the text as well).</p>
    </body>
</html>